HEADWORD: dicotyledon
<hw>di*cot`y*le"don</hw>
<pr>(d⟦isl⟧*k⟦ocr⟧t`⟦icr⟧*l⟦emac⟧"d⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Pref. <ets>di-</ets> + <ets>cotyledon</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant whose seeds divide into two seed lobes,
or cotyledons, in germinating.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> dicot, dicotyl.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

